					<head>Hagadah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79084774" rend="visible">
						<summary>Hagadah for Passover with the commentaries of Isaac Abravanel, and an allegorical interpretation of the Passover ordinances.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="yi-Hebr">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n79084774">
							<locus from="1r" to="55v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Hagadah shel Pesaḥ</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">הגדה של פסח</title>
							<decoNote type="initial">1 illustrated title page in colours and gold.<locus n="1r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="miniature">18 miniatures in colours and gold. <locus n="2v, 6v, 7v, 9r, 10r, 11v, 12v, 13v, 15v, 16r, 16v, 17r, 19v, 21r, 21v, 34v, 47r, 54r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="marginal">4 historiated initials. <locus n="2r, 4r, 4v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">6 decorated initial-words and initial-word panels in ink and gold.<locus n="5r, 33r, 46r, 49r, 51v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<note>
								<p>Contains the liturgy according to both Ashkenazi and Sefardi rites.</p>
								<p>The rubrical directions are given both in German and Spanish, the semi-cursive script being used in each. </p>
								<p>See <ref target="IMJ" type="number">6 (1987), 83-94</ref>, <ref target="Artibus&amp;historiae" type="number">9 (1988), 71-81</ref>, <ref target="Quaerendo" type="number">20 (1990), 24-62</ref>, <ref target="BrLibJournal" type="number">21 (1995), 81-108</ref>, <ref target="Fishof_1999" type="page">352</ref>, <ref target="Tahan_2007" type="page">142-143</ref>. </p>
							</note>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">ע"י הכותב והעוסק במלאכת הקדוש נאו' הקטן <name type="person" role="scribe">יאקב במהרי"ל זצ"ל מברלין</name>: לע"ע סופר סת"ם ב'ק'ק' <name type="place">המבורג </name>ו<name type="place">באלטונא</name> יע"א בשנת<date when="1740" calendar="Hebrew"> ת"ק </date>לפק.</colophon>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/36986982">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/36986982" xml:lang="en">Abravanel, Isaac</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/36986982" xml:lang="he">אברבנאל, יצחק בן יהודה </persName>
							</author>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="1r" to="26v"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush ʿal-pi ha-sod</title>
								<note>
									<p>A mystical interpretation of hagadah.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="26v" to="30r"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Seder birkat ha-mazon ke-minhag ashkenazim</title>
								<note>
									<p>Accompanied with Yiddish rendering.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="30r" to="45r"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Seder birkat ha-mazon ke-minhag sefardim</title>
								<note>
									<p>Accompanied with Yiddish rendering.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="45r" to="55v"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Remazim le-mitsvot shel Pesaḥ</title>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 18th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent>55 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>230</height>
										<width>165</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>150</height>
										<width>105</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>55 folios (+ 3 modern and 1 older unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end); folio 55 is a foliated paper flyleaf.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>26 quires: i4-2 (folios 1-2), ii-xii2 (folios 3-24), xiii4-1 (folios 25-27), xiv-xvii2 (folios 28-35), xviii4-1 (folios 36-38), xix-xxvi2 (folios 39-54).</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines=" 10 30" writtenLines=" 10 30">
									<p>Pricking and ruling are visible. </p>
									<p>Watermark, iv recto, of a fleur-de-lis and the monogram 'B. W'. Watermark, [56], of the words 'Budgen &amp; Willmott'. </p>
									<p>The square and semi-cursive scripts are imitations of the Amsterdam letters and Rashi script respectively used in printing.</p>
									<p>Many marginal illuminations and illustrations, which consist mainly of gold and coloured designs.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Ashkenazi punctuated square and unpunctuated semi-cursive script. <name type="person" role="scribe">Yaʿaḳov Sofer ben Yudah Loev</name> of <name type="place">Berlin</name>, inscribed with his name on the title page and in the colophon, <name type="place">Hamburg </name>and <name type="place">Altona </name>
								<date calendar="Hebrew">[5]500</date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">1740</date>) (folios 1r, 54v).</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Owners' notes, folios 54v-55r.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Zelig Shelomoh Zalman ha-Kohen</name> of Brandenburg: mentioned in the colophon (folio 54v). </p>
							<p>A note by Frederic Madden: 'See another and finer copy of this work in MS Sloane 3173' (folio 55v).</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Brown leather with gold-tooled.</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
